# branch: the TOTAL Branch. tag t < n routes to payload lane t+1; an out-of-range tag lands in
# lane 0 (Oob) carrying the bad tag — no panic, the index/ParseU64 discipline. Here tags are the
# element values [0..5); `branch 3` keeps 0,1,2 (lanes 1,2,3) and routes 3,4 to Oob. The clean
# `branch` would be reachable only once a range pass proves tags < n; until then this is how you split.
# n = 5
# = Sum tags=[1] [⊥, ()x1]
input iota map (x -> (x, x) branch 3)
